    <ingredient>2 cups fresh basil packed (can substitute half with spinach)</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1/3 cup pine nuts</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1/2 cup olive oil</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1/2 cup grated Parmesan </ingredient>
    <ingredient>3 cloves garlic crushed</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper </ingredient>

    <step>
In a blender, blend leaves and pine nuts. Once mixed add remaining ingredients and blend until all cook combined, but still has some texture remaining.
Serve mixed in with pasta or as a
dip.
